# HACKATHON MODE — 2HR CONSTRAINT

## Stack (non-negotiable, do not suggest alternatives)
- Backend: FastAPI + SQLModel + Alembic + PostgreSQL + uv (Python 3.11)
- Frontend: React 19 + TanStack Router v5 + TanStack Query + shadcn/ui + Tailwind v4 + bun
- Auth: JWT via existing useAuth hook + isLoggedIn() — DO NOT reimplement
- API client: auto-generated at src/client/ via openapi-ts — use SDK functions, never raw fetch
- Routes: TanStack file-based routing — new pages go in src/routes/_layout/[name].tsx
- DB sessions: use SessionDep from app.api.deps, never create engine directly
- Error handling: use handleError from @/utils + useCustomToast hook — never custom toast logic

## Output Rules
- Code only. No preamble, no "here's the updated file", no sign-off.
- Full files always. No `// ... rest of code`, no truncation, no placeholders.
- No TODOs. If something is needed, implement it or explicitly ask me to decide.
- One code block per file. If multiple files change, one block each, filename as comment on line 1.

## Code Rules
- YAGNI: flat over abstracted. No unnecessary services/repositories/factories for 2hr scope.
- SQLModel models: uuid PK with default_factory, created_at with utcnow default.
- Alembic migrations: always include both upgrade() and downgrade().
- FastAPI routes: HTTPException with specific status codes, never bare 500s.
- Zod schemas on frontend must satisfy the generated TypeScript type (use satisfies keyword).
- Loading states: always. Empty states: always. Error states: always. No skeleton-less pages.
- Use cn() for conditional classNames, never string concatenation.

## On Error Input
- Read the full stack trace. Fix the root cause. Do not suggest rewrites unrelated to the error.
- If the error is a type mismatch between frontend and backend, tell me to run: make generate-client

## Tests
- Every new API route gets a pytest test in the same response. Minimum: happy path + 404/422 case.
- Use the existing test fixtures (client, superuser_token_headers) from backend/tests/conftest.py.

## What NOT to do
- Do not add Sentry, logging services, or observability tooling.
- Do not suggest Docker changes.
- Do not modify routeTree.gen.ts — it is auto-generated by the Vite plugin.
- Do not add new dependencies without asking first. We have 2 hours.